# PROJECT: mcp-proxy

## Goal

MCP-servere registreret i Claude Desktop/Code spawnes som child-processes.
Når den underliggende Rust-binary ændrer sig (ny build, ny tool-liste), skal
Claude genstarte for at opdage ændringerne — selv hvis MCP-wrapperen stadig kører.
Dette er et per-server livscyklus-problem.

mcp-proxy er en tynd Tokio-baseret stdio-proxy der:
1. Holder den permanente stdio-forbindelse mod Claude (upstream)
2. Spawner og watch'er den interne Rust-binary (downstream)
3. Genstarter downstream ved binary-ændring eller crash
4. Sender `notifications/tools/list_changed` upstream efter genstart

Claude ser aldrig en disconnect. `list_changed` trigger en stille tool-refresh.

## Architecture

```
Claude Code
    │  stdio (persistent)
    ▼
[mcp-proxy]          ← Tokio async runtime
    │  stdio (respawnable)
    ▼
[din-rust-app]       ← den faktiske MCP-implementering
```

Fremtidig multi-app vision:
```
                         ┌─── [app-a]  (unix socket)
Claude --stdio--> [tokio]┤─── [app-b]  (unix socket)
                         └─── [app-c]  (unix socket)
```

Rust-appene behøver ikke kende til MCP. De eksponerer en simpel IPC-kontrakt:
```
← list_tools()     → [{ name, description, schema }]
← call_tool(name)  → result
```

Tokio-laget ejer al MCP-protokol-kompleksitet. Appene er rene.

## Components

| Komponent | Ansvar |
|---|---|
| `proxy` task | Relay stdin → downstream, downstream stdout → upstream |
| `watcher` task | `notify` crate — watch binary path for `Modify` events |
| `supervisor` task | Spawn/respawn downstream process via `tokio::process::Command` |
| `notifier` task | Send `notifications/tools/list_changed` til upstream efter respawn |

### Tokio task-graf

```
main
├── proxy_upstream_to_downstream   (tokio::spawn)
├── proxy_downstream_to_upstream   (tokio::spawn)
├── watcher                        (tokio::spawn)
└── supervisor                     ← koordinator
        ↑ channel fra watcher (binary changed / process died)
        ↓ channel til notifier (respawn done)
```

Alle tasks kommunikerer via `tokio::sync::mpsc` channels.
Supervisor holder `tokio::process::Child` handle og er eneste owner.

## Graceful respawn-sekvens

```
1. watcher detekterer binary Modify event
2. → mpsc signal til supervisor
3. supervisor: terminate downstream child (platform-specific)
4. supervisor: await child exit (timeout → force kill)
5. supervisor: spawn ny child
6. supervisor: await downstream "initialized" svar
7. supervisor: signal notifier
8. notifier: skriv list_changed til upstream stdout
```

## list_changed payload

```json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/tools/list_changed"
}
```

Sendes upstream via stdout umiddelbart efter downstream er oppe og har svaret på `initialize`.

## Konfiguration i Claude

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "min-server": {
      "command": "/path/to/mcp-proxy",
      "args": ["/path/to/min-rust-app"]
    }
  }
}
```

Proxyen tager binary-stien som første argument. Øvrige args videresendes til downstream.

## Stack

- Language: Rust 2024
- Runtime: tokio (async, full features)
- File watching: notify 6
- Serialization: serde + serde_json (kun til list_changed payload)
- CLI args: clap 4
- Type: CLI (single-crate, MCP stdio proxy)

## Structure

- src/main.rs: Entry point — tokio runtime, clap args
- src/adapter/: _adp hub — coordinates all layers
- src/core/: _core — supervisor, watcher, respawn logic
- src/gateway/: _gtw — IO: process spawn, file watch, stdio relay
- src/pal/: _pal — platform abstraction (process termination)
- src/shared/: _x — errors, results, shared traits
- doc/: arkitekturdokumentation (kilde)
- proj/: projekt-tracking

## Method

- Workflow: PROJECT → PHASES → TODO → code → test → DONE
- Testing: cargo test

## Patterns

- Proxy er JSON-agnostisk — relay'er bytes, konstruerer kun `list_changed`
- Alle tokio tasks kommunikerer via `tokio::sync::mpsc` channels
- Supervisor er eneste owner af `tokio::process::Child` handle
- Graceful respawn: terminate → timeout → force kill → spawn ny → await initialized → list_changed
- Ingen tung MCP-SDK — proxyen er ~150 linjer, ingen forretningslogik

## Scope

- Løser hot-reload af enkelt-servers ved code/binary ændringer
- Løser IKKE add/remove af servere til Claude uden restart af Claude selv
- Bevidst minimalt

## Fremtidigt

- Unix socket transport som alternativ til stdio-relay (bedre for debugging)
- Health-check ping til downstream for crash-detection uden file-watch
- Shared proxy-binary der konfigureres via argument (samme binary, mange servers)
- Multi-app: apps registrerer sig hos proxyen ved opstart (service mesh i miniformat)

